<blockquote><div><cite>AurorusVox wrote:</cite><blockquote><div><cite>gorilla wrote:</cite>hey shift<br>
@Otolia, there's nothing wrong with joking but remember, unlike IRL mafia, we don't see facial expressions, gestures, or vocal tone online. So when you make a post that does not resemble a joke, we aren't going to think it's a joke. To me it seems you're being dishonest about whether it was intended as a joke initially or not.
</div></blockquote></div></blockquote>
I don't like jokes in mafia simply because they are hard to read. I have seen scum use them countless times to inject their real opinion/ message to partner, and come back later and say that it was just a joke, not that you did that... but After being burned by it a few times I started to pay attention. Also, keep in mind that you are most likely the only french player on the site (and that's a good thing because we want more international players!), and thus we may not get a joke that would otherwise be obvious to a native Frenchman. Its all most like writing a poem in a different language, you can still get what each word says, but it might not rhyme any more. Not to discourage you from playing but in the early game it is a bit of a perfectionist hunt because un-like in RL we don't have anything else to go on (tone, posture, expressions, et.).<br>
<br>
@gandy, Doesn't being out of rvs imply that their is someone good enough to vote for to stop random voting? You seem to be dodging around the main point of what rvs is. RVS is a time where we random vote to pressure a player to start the content ball rolling. Once that happens "real" votes are placed, because we have something to go on. You can't have any "real" reads in rvs, and you must have some "real" reads out of rvs, because you have content that allows you to make a real vote, otherwise you would just random vote because there isn't enough content to form a read for a  "real" vote. I don't like how you responded to my post so my vote stays for now.

